{"TopicId":209062,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Better staging","CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T02:58:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T02:58:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think KSP 2 needs better staging a more Spaceflight simulator style, but mixed with original KSP style, so we can add engines twice for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s with both vacuum and atmospheric engines we can press space and the atmo engines will turn off while the vac engines turn on. and of course better staging order.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-07-21T02:58:33Z\u0022 title=\u002207/21/2022 02:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 21, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Ryaja\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ERun on sentences FTW\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ember12","CreatedById":217583,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T03:10:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree.\u00A0 In general, it would be useful for things that are now in action groups (i.e. opening solar panels, shutting off engines, deploying landing legs, etc.) to be accessible in the staging lineup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James M","CreatedById":167171,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T03:40:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you give an example on how exactly you\u0027d improve upon the staging system? From my perspective, action groups give the player all the versatility they would ever need. Furthermore they\u0027re editable during flight?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T03:45:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658374848\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James M\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, James M said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you give an example on how exactly you\u0027d improve upon the staging system? From my perspective, action groups give the player all the versatility they would ever need. Furthermore they\u0027re editable during flight?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit would just change that to a one button control basically (But there still would be action groups).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James M","CreatedById":167171,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T03:47:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156539\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658375146\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221431\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ryaja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Ryaja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit would just change that to a one button control basically (But there still would be action groups).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003ELike the spacebar?\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0Even in SFS, don\u0027t you still have to tap on the engines to turn them on or off? Is there some way in that game to turn a group off and another different group on? I don\u0027t remember that game having any action group type thingies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-07-21T03:49:55Z\u0022 title=\u002207/21/2022 03:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 21, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by James M\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T04:02:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156541\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658375271\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James M\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, James M said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003ELike the spacebar?\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0Even in SFS, don\u0027t you still have to tap on the engines to turn them on or off? Is there some way in that game to turn a group off and another different group on? I don\u0027t remember that game having any action group type thingies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey added staging\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-21T09:17:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156541\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658375271\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James M\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, James M said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003ELike the spacebar?\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0Even in SFS, don\u0027t you still have to tap on the engines to turn them on or off? Is there some way in that game to turn a group off and another different group on? I don\u0027t remember that game having any action group type thingies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSFS now lets you stage any part that has an action. There\u0027s no reason you shouldn\u0027t be able to add e.g. solar panels to the staging list of a vessel in KSP as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-22T05:40:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658395027\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s no reason you shouldn\u0027t be able to add e.g. solar panels to the staging list of a vessel in KSP as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEspecially if you have \u0022one time\u0022 functions like solar panel extension after being deployed. It\u0027d also be interesting to have certain parts be stageable multiple times, like science equipment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m starting to think that stages need to have labels instead of dumb numbers counting down to 0. Also; with numbers as a default, start from 1 and count up, not count down!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T02:45:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658373025\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ember12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/21/2022 at 6:10 AM, Ember12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit would be useful for things that are now in action groups (i.e. opening solar panels, shutting off engines, deploying landing legs, etc.) to be accessible in the staging lineup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T03:39:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156838\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658468415\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027d also be interesting to have certain parts be stageable multiple times\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you could also stage engines multiple times to turn them on and off\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156838\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658468415\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlike science equipment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I never thought about science equipment in staging. That\u0027s a really good idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T03:54:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022220957\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5219809252\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/207718-scripting-in-ksp-2/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexpanding on this idea the staging could activate different parts of scripts or different scripts, so stage 1 activates a basic launch script and that goes to orbit, stage 2 intercepts the mun, stage 3 lands, and stage 4 drives a rover to points of interest.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you would of course have to code everything yourself so it is not just a button to do it for you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-07-23T05:23:37Z\u0022 title=\u002207/23/2022 05:23  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 23, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Ryaja\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T19:16:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658395027\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/21/2022 at 5:17 AM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ne.g. solar panels to the staging list of a vessel in KSP as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell then you could\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eopen\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0them with staging but what about closing them?\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658548468\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221431\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ryaja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Ryaja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexpanding on this idea the staging could activate different parts of scripts or different scripts, so stage 1 activates a basic launch script and that goes to orbit, stage 2 intercepts the mun, stage 3 lands, and stage 4 drives a rover to points of interest.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you would of course have to code everything yourself so it is not just a button to do it for you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis would probably completely change the direction of the development and make a\u00A0\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHUGE\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0delay. Why not just wait for a ksp2 mod like that or make one yourself when it comes out?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T19:37:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157228\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658603801\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthvader15001\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, darthvader15001 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell then you could\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eopen\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0them with staging but what about closing them?\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell... Ya\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157228\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658603801\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthvader15001\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, darthvader15001 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis would probably completely change the direction of the development and make a\u00A0\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHUGE\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0delay. Why not just wait for a ksp2 mod like that or make one yourself when it comes out?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless #1 it is already being made #2 it could be a future update. If not I better learn how to code mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ember12","CreatedById":217583,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T20:09:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157228\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658603801\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthvader15001\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, darthvader15001 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell then you could\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eopen\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0them with staging but what about closing them?\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf all actions could be activated by staging, then you could close them, toggle them, anything.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T20:16:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157228\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658603801\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthvader15001\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, darthvader15001 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658395027\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/21/2022 at 10:17 AM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ne.g. solar panels to the staging list of a vessel in KSP as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell then you could\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eopen\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0them with staging but what about closing them?\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen assign the close action to a stage instead of an action group. I don\u0027t see the need to restrict stages just to engines and decouplers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T20:37:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only important downsides I see here are over cluttering and over complication for beginners. The clutter can be solved with standard good UI, and for over complication, have it so that \u201Cessential components\u201D (like in KSP 1) are automatically added to the stages, and other actions are tucked inside a different interface so that a new player isn\u2019t swarmed with icons and buttons right away. The upsides are great, as a framework that allows any action to be run using staging means adding new parts only requires additional effort to add to the staging list if new icons need to be drawn to represent actions, and it creates opportunities for UI parallel between stating and action groups.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T21:23:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157253\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658607410\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n59 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen assign the close action to a stage instead of an action group. I don\u0027t see the need to restrict stages just to engines and decouplers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut aren\u0027t \u0027stages\u0027, by their nature, one time sequential events?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat could be a bit inconvenient for things like solar panels.\u00A0 Surely an Action Group is a better solution for them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T21:43:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658611381\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut aren\u0027t \u0027stages\u0027, by their nature, one time sequential events?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs having \u0027deploy panels with fairing sep\u0027 on Stage n\u002B1 and \u0027retract panels for re-entry\u0027 on Stage n\u002B2 not an option? Why should I not be allowed to have my panels open/close with other important parts that already have staging support?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658611381\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat could be a bit inconvenient for things like solar panels.\u00A0 Surely an Action Group is a better solution for them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgain, I don\u0027t see the point in such pointless restrictions. You only have so many action groups, anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T22:34:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClearly we should be able to add actions and action groups to stages.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-23T23:08:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658615681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClearly we should be able to add actions and action groups to stages.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-24T00:09:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658611381\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat could be a bit inconvenient for things like solar panels.\u00A0 Surely an Action Group is a better solution for them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree. Also, it would be cool to have any extendable part other than airbrakes automagically retract when you enter the atmo and legs and landing gears extend like 1300 m off the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-24T00:20:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658621344\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthvader15001\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, darthvader15001 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree. Also, it would be cool to have any extendable part other than airbrakes automagically retract when you enter the atmo and legs and landing gears extend like 1300 m off the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be toggleable right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-24T00:55:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nidk cause im not a dev btw but it should be toggleable for the hardcore players (not me\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Turtlegirl1209","CreatedById":222209,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-24T12:52:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224156530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658373025\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ember12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/21/2022 at 5:10 AM, Ember12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree.\u00A0 In general, it would be useful for things that are now in action groups (i.e. opening solar panels, shutting off engines, deploying landing legs, etc.) to be accessible in the staging lineup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you could set action groups to the staging window? Including custom groups, of course! I think this would be a wonderful solution\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ember12","CreatedById":217583,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-24T15:06:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224157411\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221658667128\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222209\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Turtlegirl1209\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Turtlegirl1209 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you could set action groups to the staging window? Including custom groups, of course! I think this would be a wonderful solution\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat wouldn\u0027t be as flexible as just assigning the actions themselves.\u00A0 Assigning the actions, rather than groups, to staging means you can free up more action groups for other purposes, things you have to do more than once.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}